    <section id="t1" class="policy-section">
      <h2>1. Acceptance of Terms</h2>
      <p>By accessing or using the KingWorX website at <strong>kingworx.com.au</strong> (the "Site") or placing an order, you agree to be bound by these Terms of Service ("Terms"). If you do not agree to these Terms, please do not use our Site or services.</p>
      <p>We reserve the right to update these Terms at any time. Continued use of the Site after changes constitutes your acceptance of the revised Terms.</p>
    </section>

    <section id="t2" class="policy-section">
      <h2>2. About KingWorX</h2>
      <p>KingWorX Pty Ltd is an Australian company that designs, imports, and sells automotive performance and aero parts. Our designs are CAD-engineered in Australia and manufactured by selected partners overseas to our precise specifications.</p>
    </section>

    <section id="t3" class="policy-section">
      <h2>3. Products &amp; Fitment</h2>
      <h3>3.1 Fitment Responsibility</h3>
      <p>It is your responsibility to verify that a part is compatible with your specific vehicle before purchasing. While we provide fitment guides and model compatibility information in good faith, fitment can vary based on manufacturing year, trim level, regional specification, and prior modifications.</p>
      <p>If you are unsure, contact us before ordering. We are happy to advise. KingWorX is not liable for parts purchased for an incompatible vehicle where the customer failed to verify compatibility.</p>
      <h3>3.2 Performance Parts Disclaimer</h3>
      <p>Some parts sold by KingWorX are designed for motorsport or track use. It is your sole responsibility to ensure that any parts you install comply with applicable road laws, vehicle registration standards, and safety regulations in your state or territory. KingWorX accepts no liability for use of parts in a manner that is unlawful or contrary to manufacturer instructions.</p>
      <h3>3.3 Product Descriptions</h3>
      <p>We endeavour to ensure product descriptions and images are accurate. Colours may appear differently on screen. Specifications may change without notice. If you receive a product materially different from what was described, your rights under the Australian Consumer Law apply.</p>
    </section>

    <section id="t4" class="policy-section">
      <h2>4. Ordering &amp; Payment</h2>
      <h3>4.1 Order Acceptance</h3>
      <p>Placing an order constitutes an offer to purchase. Your order is accepted when we send you an order confirmation email and process payment. We reserve the right to refuse or cancel any order, including due to product availability, pricing errors, or suspected fraud.</p>
      <h3>4.2 Payment Methods</h3>
      <p>We accept Visa, Mastercard, American Express, PayPal, and Afterpay (where available). All transactions are processed in Australian Dollars (AUD). Payment must be made in full before orders are dispatched.</p>
      <h3>4.3 GST</h3>
      <p>All prices displayed on our Site include GST (Goods and Services Tax) where applicable, as required under Australian law.</p>
    </section>

    <section id="t5" class="policy-section">
      <h2>5. Pricing</h2>
      <p>Prices are subject to change without notice. The price charged for an order is the price displayed at the time of checkout. In the event of a pricing error, we will contact you before processing your order. You may choose to proceed at the correct price or cancel the order for a full refund.</p>
    </section>

    <section id="t6" class="policy-section">
      <h2>6. Order Cancellations</h2>
      <p>Orders may be cancelled within <strong>2 hours</strong> of placement by contacting us at <a href="mailto:orders@kingworx.com.au">orders@kingworx.com.au</a>. Once an order has been processed or dispatched, it cannot be cancelled and must be returned in accordance with our <a href="/policies/refund-policy">Returns Policy</a>.</p>
    </section>

    <section id="t7" class="policy-section">
